'''NovoGen''' is a proprietary form of [[3D printing]] technology that allows scientists to assemble living tissue cells into a desired pattern. When combined with an [[extracellular matrix]], the cells can be arranged into complex structures, such as [[Organ (anatomy)|organs]]. Designed by [[Organovo]],<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.organovo.com/|title = <nowiki>Structurally and functionally accurate bioprinted human tissue models | Organovo</nowiki>|accessdate = December 31, 2013|date = aft. December 9, 2013|publisher = Organovo|deadurl = no|archiveurl = https://archive.today/20131231135316/http://www.organovo.com/|archivedate = December 31, 2013|df = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ted.com/talks/andras_forgacs_leather_and_meat_without_killing_animals.html|title = Andras Forgacs: Leather and meat without killing animals|accessdate = December 31, 2013|date = September 2013|last = Forgacs|first = Andras|website = TED: Ideas worth spreading|archiveurl = https://archive.today/20130922003751/http://www.ted.com/talks/andras_forgacs_leather_and_meat_without_killing_animals.html|archivedate = September 22, 2013|deadurl = no|df = }}</ref> the NovoGen technology has been successfully integrated by [[Invetech]] with a production printer that is intended to help develop processes for tissue repair and organ development.<ref>{{Cite news|title = 3D Bioprinters|date = December 18, 2009|url = http://nextbigfuture.com/2009/12/3d-bioprinters.html|archiveurl = https://archive.today/20131231141054/http://nextbigfuture.com/2009/12/3d-bioprinters.html|archivedate = December 31, 2013|accessdate = December 31, 2013|last = Wang|first = Brian|deadurl = no|df = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://lifescientist.com.au/content/biotechnology/news/invetech-helps-bring-bio-printers-to-life-413047968|title = Invetech helps bring bio-printers to life|archiveurl = https://archive.today/20131231141458/http://lifescientist.com.au/content/biotechnology/news/invetech-helps-bring-bio-printers-to-life-413047968|deadurl = no|archivedate = December 31, 2013|date = December 11, 2009|accessdate = December 31, 2013|website = Australian Life Scientist|publisher = [[Westwick-Farrow Media]]|df = }}</ref>

